BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: HEART OF FLORIDA HEALTH CENTER INC

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH OF THE MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATION IN AND AROUND MARION COUNTY, FLORIDA BY PROVIDING PREVENTIVE AND PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO SUCH PERSONS IN A MANNER THAT WILL BEST MEET THEIR NEEDS AND REGARDLESS OF THE ABILITY OF AN INDIVIDUAL OR FAMILY TO PAY AND OTHER CRITICAL COMMUNITY AND SOCIAL SERVICES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: TO IMPROVE THE HEALTH OF THE MEDICALLY UNDERSERVED POPULATION IN AND AROUND MARION COUNTY, FLORIDA BY PROVIDING PREVENTIVE AND PRIMARY HEALTH CARE SERVICES TO SUCH PERSONS IN A MANNER THAT WILL BEST MEET THEIR NEEDS AND REGARDLESS OF THE ABILITY OF AN INDIVIDUAL OR FAMILY TO PAY AND OTHER CRITICAL COMMUNITY AND SOCIAL SERVICES.
IRS990.Desc: HEART OF FLORIDA HEALTH CENTER (HFHC) IS A NOT-FOR-PROFIT, 501(C)(3) ORGANIZATION THAT PROVIDES PRIMARY HEALTH CARE, DENTAL CARE AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES TO RESIDENTS WHO RECEIVE MEDICAID, MEDICARE, ARE UNINSURED, OR HAVE SOME COMMERCIAL INSURANCES. MOST OF HFHC'S PATIENTS ARE LOW INCOME. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR ENDED 2/28/2023, HFHC PROVIDED APPROXIMATELY 120,000 MEDICAL/DENTAL/BEHAVIORAL HEALTH VISITS SERVING APPROXIMATELY 33,000 PATIENTS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: HEART OF FLORIDA HEALTH CENTER (HFHC) PROVIDES, ENSURES AND ADMINISTERS ALL HEALTH CARE SERVICES FOR THE INMATES OF THE MARION COUNTY JAIL AND THE SUMTER COUNTY JAIL.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION IS A TAX-EXEMPT ORGANIZATION UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE. ACCORDINGLY, INCOME EARNED IN THE FURTHERANCE OF THE ORGANIZATION'S TAX-EXEMPT PURPOSE IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES AND THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS CONTAIN NO PROVISION OR LIABILITY FOR INCOME TAXES. THE ORGANIZATION FILES INCOME TAX RETURNS IN THE U.S. FEDERAL JURISDICTION. THE ORGANIZATION'S RETURNS FOR THE PAST THREE YEARS ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY TAX AUTHORITIES AND MAY CHANGE UPON EXAMINATION. THE ORGANIZATION HAS REVIEWED AND EVALUATED THE RELEVANT TECHNICAL MERITS OF EACH OF ITS TAX POSITIONS IN ACCORDANCE WITH ACCOUNTING PRINCIPLES GENERALLY ACCEPTED IN THE UNITED STATES OF AMERICA FOR ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES, AND DETERMINED THAT THERE ARE NO UNCERTAIN TAX POSITIONS THAT WOULD HAVE A MATERIAL IMPACT ON THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS OF THE ORGANIZATION.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION A, LINE 1A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL CONSIST OF THE OFFICERS OF THE CORPORATION AND THE CHAIRMEN OF ALL STANDING COMMITTEES. THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR SHALL BE AN EX-OFFICIO, NONVOTING MEMBER OF THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE. THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL HAVE ALL OF THE POWERS OF THE GOVERNING BOARD WHEN THE BOARD IS NOT IN SESSION, TO THE EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, AND SHALL GENERALLY PERFORM SUCH DUTIES AND EXERCISE SUCH POWERS AS MAY BE PERFORMED AND EXERCISED BY THE GOVERNING BOARD DURING THE INTERIM PERIODS BETWEEN MEETINGS OF THE BOARD, CONSISTENT WITH ESTABLISHED BOARD POLICY AND DIRECTION. SPECIFICALLY, THE EXECUTIVE COMMITTEE SHALL: (I) DEVELOP THE BOARD WORK PLAN FOR THE YEAR, INCLUDING TRAINING AND DEVELOPMENT FOR THE DIRECTORS; AND (II) CONDUCT THE PRELIMINARY EVALUATION OF THE EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR AND SHALL MAKE RECOMMENDATIONS TO THE FULL BOARD ACCORDINGLY.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE FINANCE COMMITTEE REVIEWS, APPROVES, AND PRESENTS THE FORM 990 TO THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. THE MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS REVIEW THE FORM 990 PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY IS ENFORCED BY REQUIRING BOARD MEMBERS TO DISCLOSE CONFLICTS PRIOR TO TAKING A VOTE. IF ANY CONFLICTS ARE IDENTIFIED, SUCH BOARD MEMBER WILL RECUSE HIMSELF FROM THE VOTE.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE COMPENSATION FOR THE CEO IS DETERMINED BY THE BOARD USING FLORIDA ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS (FACHC) AND NATIONAL ASSOCIATION OF COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTERS (NACHC) SALARY SURVEYS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION MAKES ITS GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AVAILABLE TO THE PUBLIC UPON REQUEST.
